prompt:
Add a public function called ComputeWithTemp to Calculator.calr that uses local variable bindings in a computation. It takes i32 parameters a and b and returns i32. Compute (a + b) * (a - b) using intermediate variables.

Use this exact Calor variable binding syntax:
§F{f003:ComputeWithTemp:pub}
  §I{i32:a}
  §I{i32:b}
  §O{i32}
  §B{sum} (+ a b)
  §B{diff} (- a b)
  §R (* sum diff)
§/F{f003}

The §B{name} expression syntax creates an immutable variable binding:
- name is the variable identifier
- expression is evaluated and bound to the name
- The variable can be used in subsequent expressions
